        <h1>EduTrack User Manual</h1>

        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>Welcome to EduTrack! This platform is designed to manage educational records efficiently. Whether you are a student, GFM (Guardian Faculty Member), or an administrator, this guide will help you navigate the system.</p>

        <h2>2. Getting Started</h2>
        <h3>2.1 System Requirements</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Latest version of Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, or Microsoft Edge</li>
            <li>Stable internet connection</li>
            <li>JavaScript enabled</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>2.2 Accessing the System</h3>
        <p>To access EduTrack, visit the <a href="/">login page</a> and enter your credentials.</p>

        <h2>3. User Roles</h2>
        <p>EduTrack supports different user roles:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><b>Students:</b> Can view and update their educational details.</li>
            <li><b>GFM:</b> Can manage student records and academic progress.</li>
            <li><b>Administrator:</b> Manages the overall system settings.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Registration and Login</h2>
        <h3>4.1 Creating an Account</h3>
        <p>To sign up, go to the <a href="/sign">Signup Page</a> and fill in the required details.</p>
        <h3>4.2 Logging In</h3>
        <p>Enter your <b>username</b> and <b>password</b> on the login page to access your dashboard.</p>

        <h2>5. Dashboard</h2>
        <p>After logging in, you will be directed to your dashboard, which contains:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Personal Details</li>
            <li>Academic Records</li>
            <li>Notifications and Announcements</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Managing Your Account</h2>
        <h3>6.1 Updating Profile</h3>
        <p>Users can update their details in the "Profile" section.</p>
        <h3>6.2 Resetting Password</h3>
        <p>If you forget your password, use the "Forgot Password" option on the login page.</p>

        <h2>7. Data Entry</h2>
        <h3>7.1 Student Data Entry</h3>
        <p>Students must provide details such as:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Full Name</li>
            <li>RBT Number</li>
            <li>Email ID</li>
            <li>Phone Number</li>
            <li>Department</li>
            <li>Passout Batch</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.2 GFM Data Entry</h3>
        <p>GFMs must enter their:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Full Name</li>
            <li>Username</li>
            <li>Password</li>
            <li>Phone Number</li>
            <li>Email ID</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Security and Privacy</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>All passwords are encrypted for security.</li>
            <li>User data is stored securely in the database.</li>
            <li>Always log out after using the system to prevent unauthorized access.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>9. Troubleshooting</h2>
        <h3>9.1 Login Issues</h3>
        <p>Ensure that your username and password are correct. If you forgot your password, use the "Forgot Password" option.</p>
        <h3>9.2 Data Not Saving</h3>
        <p>Ensure all required fields are filled in correctly. Check your internet connection.</p>

        <h2>10. Contact Support</h2>
        <p>If you experience any issues, contact the EduTrack support team .</p>
